	<p>Create a HTML page, when it opens in Browser, it should prompt twice. Once for first name and second for last name. When you enter first and last name, it should alert you as "Hello firstname lastname."</p>
	<p>After alert it should put that text in html page</p>
	<div class="solution">
	  	<script type="text/javascript">
		  function load01(){
		    var fname=prompt("Enter first Name");
		    if(fname=="" || fname==null)
		    {
		     alert("you cant left the Field empty");
		     fname=prompt("Enter first Name");
		    }


		    var lname=prompt("Enter Last Name"); 
		       if(lname=="" || lname==null)
		       {
		         alert("you cant left the Field empty");
		         lname=prompt("Enter last Name");
		      }

		    alert("Hello " + fname + " " + lname);
		    document.write("Hello " + fname + " " + lname);   
		} 
		window.load=load01();
	</script>
